                  <persName corresp="PRS0000" instant="false" full="yes">The name of the original donor(s) was probably written in the erased part of Additio 1 and in the supplication formulas throughout the Ms. &#xD;
According to Additio 2, Zä-Śǝllase donated the Ms. to the church of ʾIyäsus (Gwaḥgot) in 1901/02. His name and the name of his wife Wälättä Rufaʾel are also written in the supplication formulas, over the erased name(s), in the same hand as Additio 2 (e.g., fols. 7ra, 32ra). Two other names, &lt;...&gt; Mikaʾel and his wife Ṣädalä Maryam, are added in some supplication formulas, in another secondary hand (e.g., fols. 25ra, 37va).</persName>
